# Tnh ton s lng ct ca mi DataFrame
num_columns = [len(data.columns) for data in dataframes]

# Tnh ton s lng dng null ca mi DataFrame
num_null_rows = [data.isnull().any(axis=1).sum() for data in dataframes]

# Tnh ton s lng ct null ca mi DataFrame
num_null_columns = [data.isnull().any(axis=0).sum() for data in dataframes]

# To DataFrame t cc gi tr  tnh c
overview_data_general = pd.DataFrame({
    'Dataset': dataframe_names,
    'Number of Rows': num_rows,
    'Number of Columns': num_columns,
    'Number of Null Rows': num_null_rows,
    'Number of Null Columns': num_null_columns
})

print("Overview Data:")
print(overview_data_general)

# Column name, data type, % null, s lng category
# Tnh ton cc gi tr cho mi DataFrame
dataframes = [Customers, Geolocation, orderItems, orderPayments, orderReviews, Orders, Products, Sellers, categoryNameTranslation]
dataframe_names = ['Customers', 'Geolocation', 'Order Items', 'Order Payments', 'Order Reviews', 'Orders', 'Products', 'Sellers', 'Category Translation']

column_names = []
data_types = []
percent_null = []
num_categories = []

for data in dataframes:
    column_names.append(list(data.columns))
    data_types.append(list(data.dtypes))
    percent_null.append((data.isnull().mean() * 100).tolist())
    num_categories.append([data[column].nunique() for column in data.columns])

# To DataFrame mi t cc gi tr tnh c
data_info_general = pd.DataFrame({
    'Dataset': sum([[name]*len(columns) for name, columns in zip(dataframe_names, column_names)], []),
    'Column Name': sum(column_names, []),
    'Data Type': sum(data_types, []),
    '% Null': sum(percent_null, []),
    'Number of Categories': sum(num_categories, [])
})

# Hin th kt qu
print("Data Information:")
print(data_info_general)

#Khong thi gian thu thp d liu
# To DataFrame date_info
date_info = pd.DataFrame(columns=['Dataset', 'Start date', 'End date'])

# To danh sch cc DataFrame v tn ca chng
dataframes = [Customers, Geolocation, orderItems, orderPayments, orderReviews, Orders, Products, Sellers, categoryNameTranslation]
dataframe_names = ['Customers', 'Geolocation', 'Order Items', 'Order Payments', 'Order Reviews', 'Orders', 'Products', 'Sellers', 'Category Translation']

# Tn ct ngy thng trong cc DataFrame khc
date_column_names = [None, None, 'shipping_limit_date', None, 'review_creation_date', 'order_purchase_timestamp', None, None, None]

# Kim tra v thm thng tin cho mi DataFrame
for dataframe, dataframe_name, date_column_name in zip(dataframes, dataframe_names, date_column_names):
    if date_column_name is not None and date_column_name in dataframe.columns:
        start_date = dataframe[date_column_name].min()
        end_date = dataframe[date_column_name].max()
    else:
        start_date = None
        end_date = None
    
    date_info = pd.concat([date_info, pd.DataFrame({'Dataset': [dataframe_name], 'Start date': [start_date], 'End date': [end_date]})], ignore_index=True)

# Hin th kt qu
print("Date Information:")
print(date_info)

#6.3 average delay for delivery (days)
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
# Tnh thi gian ch i giao hng
order_Customer_merge['order_delivered_customer_date'] = pd.to_datetime(order_Customer_merge['order_delivered_customer_date'])
order_Customer_merge['order_purchase_timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(order_Customer_merge['order_purchase_timestamp'])

#6.4 average difference between delivery & estimated date (days)
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Tnh s khc bit gia thi gian giao hng thc t v d kin
Orders['order_delivered_customer_date'] = pd.to_datetime(Orders['order_delivered_customer_date'])
Orders['order_estimated_delivery_date'] = pd.to_datetime(Orders['order_estimated_delivery_date'])
Orders['delivery_difference'] = (Orders['order_estimated_delivery_date'] - Orders['order_delivered_customer_date']).dt.days

#7.3 compare order purchase by year month (201701,201702,201703,...) of different payment types in the same chart
#Tnh tng s n hng cho mi thng canm cho tng loi thanh ton
# Chuyn sang nh dng datetime
merged_data['order_purchase_timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(merged_data['order_purchase_timestamp'])

# To ct month_year t ct order_purchase_timestamp
merged_data['month_year'] = merged_data['order_purchase_timestamp'].dt.to_period('M')

# Nhm d liu theo month_year v payment_type
order_purchase_by_month_and_payment_type = merged_data.groupby(['month_year', 'payment_type']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)

# Thm ct tng s n hng cho mi thng
order_purchase_by_month_and_payment_type['total_orders'] = order_purchase_by_month_and_payment_type.sum(axis=1)

# Ly danh sch cc loi thanh ton
payment_types = order_purchase_by_month_and_payment_type.columns[:-1].tolist()

# Reset index  chuyn month_year t index thnh ct
order_purchase_by_month_and_payment_type = order_purchase_by_month_and_payment_type.reset_index()

# Chuyn ct 'month_year' sang kiu chui
order_purchase_by_month_and_payment_type['month_year'] = order_purchase_by_month_and_payment_type['month_year'].astype(str)

# line chart
for payment_type in payment_types:
    plt.plot(order_purchase_by_month_and_payment_type['month_year'], order_purchase_by_month_and_payment_type[payment_type], label=payment_type)

plt.xlabel('Year Month')
plt.ylabel('Number of Orders')
plt.title('Comparison of Order Purchase by Year Month and Payment Type')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)  
plt.legend()
plt.show()
